Ignore verif_scale_pyperf600 on LLVM 18+

From: Shung-Hsi Yu <shung-hsi.yu@suse.com>

Since LLVM 18 verif_scale_pyperf600 test will fail due to symtab-related
changes in the output binary, no fix is available yet, so simply ignore
it when the LLVM version used is newer than 17.

Link: https://lore.kernel.org/all/Zsxd9HskofXttp+p@kodidev-ubuntu/
Signed-off-by: Shung-Hsi Yu <shung-hsi.yu@suse.com>
---
 ci/vmtest/configs/DENYLIST-6.18   |    1 +
 ci/vmtest/configs/DENYLIST-latest |    2 ++
 2 files changed, 3 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 ci/vmtest/configs/DENYLIST-6.18

diff --git a/ci/vmtest/configs/DENYLIST-6.18 b/ci/vmtest/configs/DENYLIST-6.18
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..94aca8e
--- /dev/null
+++ b/ci/vmtest/configs/DENYLIST-6.18
@@ -0,0 +1 @@
+verif_scale_pyperf600 # failing since LLVM 18+
diff --git a/ci/vmtest/configs/DENYLIST-latest b/ci/vmtest/configs/DENYLIST-latest
index e78d7f6..49d76ee 100644
--- a/ci/vmtest/configs/DENYLIST-latest
+++ b/ci/vmtest/configs/DENYLIST-latest
@@ -8,6 +8,8 @@ bpf_cookie/perf_event
 send_signal/send_signal_nmi
 send_signal/send_signal_nmi_thread
 
+
 lwt_reroute # crashes kernel, fix pending upstream
 tc_links_ingress # fails, same fix is pending upstream
 tc_redirect		  # enough is enough, banned for life for flakiness
+verif_scale_pyperf600 # failing since LLVM 18+
